    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Strengthening the border and enforcing immigration laws is crucial for national security, economic stability, and protecting American citizens' rights. Increased border security measures, such as advanced surveillance systems, drones, and physical barriers, will effectively deter and apprehend undocumented immigrants, reducing the flow of illicit goods, human trafficking, and terrorism. Stricter enforcement will also enable the removal of repeat offenders, reduce the strain on public resources, and promote a more merit-based immigration system. Furthermore, stricter enforcement will allow the US to prioritize high-skilled, high-wage immigrant workers, boosting economic growth and competitiveness.",
