      "content": "thanks. those are good foundational points. one of my students is struggling though—they're finding it hard to move past the 'security' aspect and actually engage with the socio-economic arguments. specifically, regarding the part about 'straining public resources,' could you expand on that? they want to understand the specific economic logic used by proponents of stricter enforcement so they can argue against it effectively during cross-ex.",
