      "content": "Proponents of stricter enforcement argue that increased deportations and detention costs will be offset by the economic benefits of a more efficient and streamlined immigration system. They claim that by prioritizing high-skilled workers and eliminating low-skilled, low-wage labor, businesses will be incentivized to invest in automation and technology, reducing the need for cheap labor and increasing competitiveness. Additionally, proponents argue that the economic benefits of stricter enforcement will be felt through increased tax revenue from deportees and their families, as well as reduced healthcare and social welfare costs associated with providing services to unauthorized immigrants.",
      "source": "target",
